cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a protocol layer to obfuscate transported application data to defend against active probing and fingerprinting techniques used in Internet censorship. It may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with circumventing censorship in the context of network protocols. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it proposes a solution to a problem related to distributed systems. It may also be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it proposes a new protocol layer for software systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it proposes a new protocol layer that could be implemented using programming languages.
